OL,3,CArchbishop of Canterbury considered
OL,4,Cresigning over barrister abuse cases
OL,6,FSpeaking to Channel 4 News on
OL,7,FThursday, Mr Welby said: "I have been
OL,8,Fgiving that (resigning) a lot of
OL,9,Fthought for actually quite a long
OL,10,Ftime, there is nothing over the last
OL,11,Ften years that has been as horrible as
OL,12,Fdealing with numerous abuse cases.
OL,14,F"I have given it (resigning) a lot of
OL,15,Fthought and have taken advice as
OL,16,Frecently as this morning from senior
OL,17,Fcolleagues, and, no, I am not going to
OL,18,Fresign."
OL,20,FAsked if he considered resigning on
OL,21,FThursday morning, Mr Welby said "yes".
