OL,3,CArchbishop of Canterbury considered
OL,4,Cresigning over barrister abuse cases
OL,6,FThe report said while Mr Welby knew
OL,7,FSmyth and "did have reason to have
OL,8,Fsome concern about him", this was not
OL,9,Fthe same as suspecting he had
OL,10,Fcommitted severe abuses and concluded
OL,11,Fit was "not possible to establish"
OL,12,Fwhether Mr Welby knew of the severity
OL,13,Fof the abuses in the UK before 2013.
OL,15,FSmyth "could and should have been
OL,16,Fformally reported to the police in the
OL,17,FUK, and to authorities in South Africa
OL,18,F(church authorities and potentially
OL,19,Fthe police) by church officers,
OL,20,Fincluding a diocesan bishop and Justin
OL,21,FWelby in 2013, the review said.
